params.name: data.optimize_table_operation_name
params.description: If exists, the name of the long-running operation that will be used to track the post-restore optimization process to optimize the performance of the restored table. The metadata type of the long-running operation is [OptimizeRestoreTableMetadata][]. The response type is [Empty][google.protobuf.Empty]. This operation may not be created if the table is already optimized or the restore was not successful.
